pages.text:
We are an exciting exclusive children's theatre in Jacksonville.  We offer acting, musical theatre, dance, voice and piano lessions for kids ages 4-18. 
SET Studios, acting, musical theatre, dance, voice, piano, singing, children's theatre
If you have any questions about SET, please feel free to contact us.

JOIN OUR COMPANY TEAM
This group is our elite performance team that travels all around the country!  Below is a list of incredible events that we are honored to participate in every year and have become wonderful traditions for us:
​
Jacksonville Icemen Game
, Vystar Memorial, National Anthem, November 26
Tony's Turkey Trot,
Atlantic Beach, National Anthem, November 27
Deck the Chairs
, Jacksonville Beach, Holiday Musical Revue, December 20
Junior Theatre Festival ATL,
Madagascar Jr.,
January 16-18
Junior Theatre Festival WEST,
13, the Musical,
February 6-8
Access Broadway,
New York, (tentative), March 20-22
JTF ATL
​
Junior Theatre Festival Atlanta, Cobb Galleria
Dates:
January 16-18, 2026
Who:
Kids ages 8-18 (Auditions required for new students)
Travel:
Arrive Thursday, Jan.15 or Friday by 3 PM. Return Monday, Jan. 19
JTF Fee:
$350/student, teacher, parent, sibling. (Due September 27th)
JTF Prep Fee:
$125/month ($500 if paid in full)
Rehearsals:
Saturdays, 9:30 AM-12:30 PM beginning September 27th
Agenda:
Kids will learn a 15 medley of vocals and choreography of
Madagascar Jr.
Attire:
Kids will wear jeans/leggings with JTF and SET Tshirts. (Provided)
​
**WE WILL BE HEAVILY FUNDRAISING FOR ALL OF THESE ACTIVITIES, SO WE ASK FOR FULL PARTICIPATION FROM THE PARENTS, AS WELL AS, STUDENTS.
JTF WEST
Junior Theatre Festival West, Sacramento. Memorial Auditorium
Dates:
February 6-8, 2026
Who:
Middle School and High School Students
Auditions:
September 7, 1PM.  Vocal and dance audition.
Travel
:  Thursday, Feb.5. Leave Monday, Feb 9.
JTF Fee:
$335/ student, teacher, parent, sibling. Due November 8th)
JTF Prep Fee:
$125/month ($500 if paid in full)
Discount:
If participating in both festivals, $150/month ($700 if paid in full)
Rehearsals:
Sundays, 1 PM-4 PM beginning September 28th
Agenda:
Kids will learn a 15 medley of vocals and choreography of
13, the Musical.
Attire:
Kids will wear jeans/leggings with JTF and SET Tshirts. (Provided)
**NEW WORKS SHOWCASE:
Performing a full medley production on Saturday night, Feb. 7th,
with full costumes, set pieces, and props of a hot new, high-energy Jr. Musical.  Mandatory rehearsal on Friday, Feb 6th, morning/afternoon. (Time TBD)
Suggested Dance Class:
Saturdays, 4 pm-5 pm
If you are interested in auditioning for the New Works Showcase, this class is strongly suggested! You can sign up online.
FYI:  New Works Showcase is very hip hop heavy!
AUDITIONS
Date:
Sunday, September 7
Time:
1 PM-4 PM
Who:
Middle School and High School singers, dancers, and tumblers for JTF West and/or kids ages 8+ for JTF ATL.
What to prepare:
1 minute pop/rock style song by your favorite artist or from a pop/rock musical.  Bring your own instrumental tracks.  Please download your music to your device to avoid WIFI problems. There will
NOT
be an accompanist on site.
What to wear:
Comfortable clothing and shoes.
Dance:
There will be a short dance combo audition.  Dance/fitness attire is recommended. Jazz shoes and/or sneakers are great for dance.
Optional:
Please bring headshot and resume.
Other:
Bring water, snacks, and/or money.  There are great restaurants next to us.
​
*THIS IS A CLOSED AUDITION.  FIRST COME FIRST SERVE.
​
Sunday's Schedule
12:30 - 1:00 | Sign-in/Warm-up
1:00 - 1:20 | Learn Dance Combo
1:30 - 2:15 | Vocal Auditions (First 20 kids)
2:15 - 2:45 | Dance Auditions (EVERYONE)
3:00 - 3:45 | Vocal Auditions (2nd group of kids)
​
​
​
ACCESS BROADWAY 2026
Access Broadway, Malloy College, New York
Dates:
March 20-21, 2026
Who:
Kids ages 8+ (Auditions TBD)
Agenda
:  Kids may bring solos, duets, trios, and group numbers of singing, acting, or dancing.
**Info:
This event is the week of spring break for Duval County and we could make this a fun trip to NYC. If you are interested in doing this competition, please send us an email at
info@setstudiosjax.com
Rehearsals:
Kids would have to set up private lessons with me to work on solo/duet/trio pieces. Currently Mondays and Fridays are open for private lessons...
